meta {
  name: GET notifications (v2.10.0 Group B)
  type: http
  seq: 41
}

get {
  url: {{base_url}}/v1/vehicles/{{vin}}/notifications
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
}

docs {
  v2.10.0 Group B - In-vehicle notification list.

  Returns the list of recent in-vehicle notifications. Surfaced as
  three diagnostic entities: ``notifications_count`` (int total),
  ``last_notification_subject`` (string) and
  ``last_notification_severity`` (string). All phantom-protected via
  ``_DATA_PRESENT_REQUIRED`` so other brands and vehicles without
  the endpoint stay clean.

  Endpoint reference: Timwun/Cupra-WeConnect-Bruno-Collection
  (Notifications sequence), independently parsed in
  ``seat_cupra.get_status`` v2.10.0.

  Response shape (observed across CUPRA Born + Leon):
    {
      "notifications": [
        {
          "subject": "Service due in 30 days",
          "severity": "INFO" | "WARNING" | "ALERT",
          "timestamp": "2026-05-30T18:42:11Z",
          "type": "MAINTENANCE"
        },
        ...
      ]
    }

  Some firmwares wrap the list under ``data.notifications`` or ship
  it as a bare top-level list - the parser accepts all three shapes.

  Soft-fails to ``{}`` on 401 / 403 (older firmware that does not
  expose the endpoint) and 404 (no notifications recorded for this
  VIN).
}
